entry.title: New Jerseyans Don't Pump Gas. That's Just How They Like It.
entry.content: Many Garden State residents are proud to be the last U.S. state to prohibit self-service gas stations.

entry.title: Ukraine's Ammunition Chief Battles to Boost Production
entry.content: Oleksandr Kamyshin, formerly the head of the state railway company, now faces the challenge of bringing Ukraine’s defense industry up to speed as the war with Russia drags on.

entry.title: The Era of Ultracheap Stuff Is Under Threat
entry.content: Factories across Asia are struggling to attract young workers. That’s bad news for Western consumers accustomed to inexpensive goods made in the region.
